cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.SI

This paper proposes a novel CNN-based framework with adaptive graph transforms to learn disease-relevant connectome feature maps for traditional prediction tasks. The paper focuses on neuroimaging studies and analyzing data with irregular structure such as brain connectivity. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper uses CNNs for image analysis, which falls under cs.CV (Computer Vision) and the proposed framework is supervised, which falls under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
